The paper discusses the development of an evolutionary model of adaptive behavior in a stochastic environment, which involves the use of a neuroevolutionary algorithm based on neuron duplication. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Neural and Evolutionary Computing (cs.NE) sub-category. Additionally, the paper discusses the use of recurrent neural networks, which are commonly used in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) research. The paper also discusses the emergence of behavioral strategies, which suggests that it may belong to the Learning (cs.LG) sub-category. The paper also discusses the development of agents, which suggests that it may belong to the Systems and Control (cs.SY) sub-category. Finally, the paper discusses the use of simulation, which suggests that it may belong to the Robotics (cs.RO) sub-category.
